    "causal_summary": "Four structural gaps in the generate-context.js memory pipeline degrade indexing quality and cross-session coherence without surfacing any observable errors. Embedding retry failures are silently tracked by a background job but never exposed through MCP tooling, leaving operators blind to vector-search degradation. Trigger phrase extraction produces 15-30 noisy phrases per memory dominated by path fragments and n-gram shingles, causing binary trigger matching to return low-quality results. The Mustache template renderer silently discards 15+ AI-composed fields (toolCalls, exchanges, pipeline flags), while 8 phantom V2.2 placeholders are always empty and 9 valid data-source bindings are suppressed. Cross-session dedup is purely AI-assisted: referenced memory IDs are never validated, causal links receive no graph verification, and observation arrays are deduped only within a single render pass.",
